problem statements
- networks are scanned for open ports
- ports are exposed for known vulnerabilities

solutions
> so how about a scanner that notifies the user of those vulnerabilities. 
>> can be made to explain what ports do what and why some should be open/closed/filtered.

tech specs
= nmap for open ports
== grep or awk output for ports that they need to run their service
=== and for the ports that they do not need -> alert them of unneccessary open port


features
~ user input of what they need to run on their system (eg web server)
~~ checks to see what ports they have open that are associated with their service

